cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on language modeling and generalization in seq2seq models. Additionally, the paper uses navigation instructions as a probing tool, which is a common task in natural language processing. The paper also touches on machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper's use of a grounded environment and its focus on visual inputs may also make cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of recurrent networks and its focus on navigation may make cs.RO (Robotics) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
